      "writtenOn": "2020-08-13T11:00:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "By passing callbacks to configParser, it is generally usable, but on the other hand callbacks make it more difficult to tell the actual code execution path due to indirection.\n\nGo has clear preference of simpleness and directness. So if we can avoid callbacks that would be great.\n\nIn this case, the parser is used to parse host configs only. Can we make the parser specialized for host configs and avoid callbacks?",
