      "writtenOn": "2020-08-13T11:00:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Currently we stop parsing the config files when we find the match. But can you always continue to the end?\n\nBy skipping parsing, we might miss config errors in the latter part of config files. This means that, depending on the host name the user specifies, we sometimes see config errors, sometimes not. This is a bit surprising behavior to users. Fortunately the cost is not large even if we parse all config files.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 104,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 104,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "de401b1b7b329222f060bf31339a9cf896645a5f",
